# macOS Finder / iCloud / Time Machine duplicate files (e.g., `Foo 2.cs`).
# Scoped to source-shaped extensions only — these are the file types where
# a duplicate produces real build damage (CS source: duplicate-type defs;
# MSBuild config: redefined targets; properties.json duplicate: source-gen
# crash). Per Task 18 hardening 2 review Rec 4, the patterns intentionally
# do NOT match .html / .txt / .md / .png / .pdf / etc. so legitimate
# numbered docs, fixtures, and assets (`Sample 2.html`, `screenshot 3.png`)
# are tracked normally. Directory.Build.props provides the matching
# compile-time defense for `.cs` only. Force-add a legitimately named
# numbered file with `git add -f path/to/file`.
* [0-9].cs
* 1[0-9].cs
* [0-9].csproj
* 1[0-9].csproj
* [0-9].props
* 1[0-9].props
* [0-9].targets
* 1[0-9].targets
* [0-9].json
* 1[0-9].json
